main event: An unidentified flying object was observed at Salisbury Beach, Massachusetts on 19 June 1952.
interesting points: The object was described as a round light that changed color from white to green., It made a sound similar to an aircraft engine but was quieter., The observation lasted for 1.5 minutes., The conclusion of the report suggested the object was probably an aircraft., The sighting involved civilian witnesses and occurred in an area frequently used by aircraft.
witness description: civilian observers, no specific details provided
